Subject: [PATCH] feat(proxy): embedding intent classification, provenance
 chain, belief resolution, graph-aware chunking
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- Intent classification: upgraded from keyword scan to embedding cosine similarity
  against precomputed exemplar vectors (startup). Falls back to keyword scan if
  embeddings unavailable. Also improved dependency keywords.
- Provenance chain: new build_provenance_chain() traces Chunk→Concept/Entity path
  in Neo4j and injects 'Retrieval Provenance:' into GCOR context header.
- Belief conflict resolution: resolve_belief_conflicts() picks winning belief by
  confidence then valid_from recency; injects resolution reason into context.
- Graph-aware chunking: _find_entity_boundaries() uses regex to protect person names,
  acronyms, and ISO dates from being split across chunk boundaries.
